  "prompt": "What is Fiverr, and how do they make money?",
  "response": "Fiverr is a global online marketplace that offers freelance services. Founded in 2010, it provides a platform where freelancers can offer services to customers, ranging from graphic design, writing, programming, digital marketing, video editing, music production, and more. The services offered on Fiverr are often referred to as \"gigs.\"\n\nHere\u2019s how Fiverr makes money:\n\n1. **Service Fees**: Fiverr charges a service fee for facilitating transactions between freelancers and customers. Typically, they charge buyers a fee for each purchase, which is a percentage of the gig's price. As of recent structures, the service fee for buyers is around $1 on purchases up to $40, and then 5% on purchases over $40.\n\n2. **Seller Fees**: Freelancers (sellers) also incur fees for using the platform. Fiverr takes a 20% commission off the earnings of freelancers for every gig purchased. This means if a freelancer sells a service for $100, they receive $80, and Fiverr keeps $20.\n\n3. **Subscription Plans**: Fiverr offers subscription plans like Fiverr Business designed for teams looking to manage multiple freelance projects. These plans usually come with enhanced support and collaboration tools, and users pay a monthly or annual subscription fee.\n\n4. **Promoted Gigs**: Fiverr provides an option for freelancers to promote their gigs through internal advertising. Freelancers pay a fee to Fiverr to have their services more prominently displayed, increasing visibility to potential buyers.\n\n5. **Course Fees**: Fiverr offers educational courses and certifications through \u201cLearn from Fiverr.\u201d Freelancers can pay for these courses to enhance their skills and increase the attractiveness of their profiles.\n\nBy leveraging these diverse streams, Fiverr is able to generate substantial revenue while providing a robust platform for both freelancers and businesses seeking various services.",
